SessionID()` to ensure the ID contains only path-safe characters (alphanumeric, underscores, hyphens) and rejects anything with path separators\\n2. **Git repo check** (lines 69-72): Ensures the attach happens within a git repository\\n3. **Session uniqueness check** (lines 74-85): Verifies the session isn't already tracked by querying the session state store\\n4. **Transcript existence check** (lines 94-110): Locates the agent's transcript file, with fallback to search across project directories if not found in the expected location\\n\\n**Core Processing (lines 112-248):**\\n1. **Read transcript data** (lines 112-116): Uses `ag.ReadTranscript()` to load raw transcript bytes\\n2. **Extract modified files** (lines 118-126): Calls `analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` to identify which files the agent modified\\n3. **Detect git file changes** (lines 128-141): Uses `DetectFileChanges()` to find actual file changes, then filters to only uncommitted files\\n4. **Create session metadata directory** (lines 150-172):\\n   - Creates `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/` directory\\n   - **For Gemini specifically**: Normalizes the transcript via `normalizeGeminiTranscript()` because Gemini stores user message content as arrays `[{\\\"text\\\":\\\"...\\\"}]` instead of plain strings (the UI expects strings)\\n   - Copies the transcript to the session metadata directory\\n5. **Extract first prompt** (lines 180-191): Uses `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript()` to get the initial user prompt (supports both JSONL and Gemini JSON formats)\\n6. **Initialize session state** (lines 193-197): Calls `strat.InitializeSession()` to create the session state file with basic metadata\\n7. **Enrich session state** (lines 199-202): Calls `enrichSessionState()` to populate transcript-derived metadata\\n8. **Save checkpoint** (lines 204-223): Calls `strat.SaveStep()` to create the initial checkpoint on the shadow branch\\n9. **Condense and finalize** (lines 225-316): Calls `condenseAndFinalizeSession()` to move the checkpoint to permanent metadata storage\\n\\n### 2. **Session Metadata Validation and Enrichment**\\n\\n**Initial Validation** happens in `attach.go`:\\n- Session ID format check (path-safe)\\n- Session uniqueness (not already tracked)\\n- Transcript file existence\\n\\n**Metadata Enrichment** (`enrichSessionState()`, lines 250-280 in attach.go):\\nAfter session initialization, the following metadata is extracted from the transcript and stored in the session state file:\\n\\n1. **CLI Version** (line 260): Stores the CLI version that attached the session\\n2. **Transcript Path** (line 261): The path to the live transcript file\\n3. **Token Usage** (lines 263-265): Calls `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` to compute input/output tokens from transcript data\\n4. **User Turn Count** (lines 266-268): Calls `countUserTurns()` to distinguish real user prompts from tool_result messages\\n5. **Model Name** (lines 269-271): Calls `extractModelFromTranscript()` to extract the LLM model used\\n6. **Session Duration** (lines 272-274): Calls `estimateSessionDuration()` to calculate elapsed time from transcript timestamps\\n\\n**Important Notes on Gemini:**\\n- Gemini transcripts don't include timestamps (return 0 for duration)\\n- Gemini transcripts don't store model info in the transcript itself (only in hook events) â€” so `extractModelFromTranscript()` returns empty string\\n- Gemini content format normalization is essential before storing for UI rendering\\n\\n### 3. **Gemini CLI Agent Implementation** \\n\\n**Session Detection** (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini.go`):\\n- `DetectPresence()` (lines 54-74): Checks for `.gemini/` directory or `.gemini/settings.json`\\n- `GetSessionDir()` (lines 110-124): Returns `~/.gemini/tmp/<project-hash>/chats/` where `<project-hash>` is SHA256 of the project root\\n- `ResolveSessionFile()` (lines 88-106): Searches for files matching `session-*-<first8chars>.json` pattern, falls back to constructing filename matching Gemini's convention\\n\\n**Hook Installation** (`hooks.go`, lines 45-222):\\nInstalls 12 hooks into `.gemini/settings.json`:\\n1. `SessionStart` - captures session initialization\\n2. `SessionEnd` (exit + logout matchers) - captures session termination\\n3. `BeforeAgent` / `AfterAgent` - captures user prompts and responses\\n4. `BeforeModel` / `AfterModel` - captures LLM request/response\\n5. `BeforeToolSelection` - before tool selection\\n6. `BeforeTool` / `AfterTool` - around tool execution\\n7. `PreCompress` - before chat history compression\\n8. `Notification` - error/warning events\\n\\nHooks are stored in the `hooksConfig.enabled: true` + hook matchers format.\\n\\n**Lifecycle Event Parsing** (`lifecycle.go`, lines 40-61):\\nTranslates Gemini hook input into normalized Events:\\n- `parseSessionStart()` / `parseSessionEnd()` (lines 110-161): Extracts session ID and transcript path\\n- `parseTurnStart()` (lines 123-135): Extracts user prompt from BeforeAgent hook\\n- `parseTurnEnd()` (lines 137-148): Captures agent completion\\n- `parseBeforeModel()` (lines 163-178): Extracts model name for ModelUpdate event\\n- `parseCompaction()` (lines 180-191): Captures transcript compression events\\n\\n**Transcript Parsing** (`transcript.go`, lines 89-244):\\n- `ParseTranscript()`: Unmarshals Gemini JSON into structured format\\n- `GeminiMessage.UnmarshalJSON()` (lines 35-79): **Normalizes content formats** â€” handles both `[{\\\"text\\\":\\\"...\\\"}]` (user) and string (gemini) formats, combining text blocks with newlines\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromTranscript()`: Scans gemini messages for tool calls matching `FileModificationTools` (write_file, edit_file, save_file, replace)\\n- `ExtractAllUserPromptsFromTranscript()`: Collects all user messages\\n- `CalculateTokenUsage()`: Extracts token counts from `message.tokens` field\\n\\n**Token Calculation** (`lifecycle.go`, lines 72-106):\\nFor Gemini, token usage is extracted from `geminiMessageWithTokens` struct:\\n- Input, Output, Cached tokens from each gemini message\\n- APICallCount incremented per gemini message\\n- Note: Unlike Claude (which has explicit token fields), Gemini requires parsing `tokens` object in messages\\n\\n### 4. **Metadata Validation Before Attaching**\\n\\n**Currently, there is NO explicit metadata completeness validation before attach.** The flow instead:\\n\\n1. **Best-effort extraction**: Attempts to extract available metadata (token usage, turn count, model, duration)\\n2. **Non-fatal failures**: Warns but continues if extraction fails (lines 131-132 in attach.go)\\n3. **Partial state OK**: Session can be attached with minimal metadata â€” even transcript-only sessions are valid\\n4. **No \\\"complete\\\" check**: There's no validation that requires specific fields to be present before considering the attachment successful\\n\\n**However, validation happens at specific points:**\\n- **ValidationID validation**: `validation.ValidateSessionID()` prevents path traversal\\n- **Session initialization**: `strat.InitializeSession()` validates the session isn't already tracked\\n- **Session state validation**: When loading state, `state.NormalizeAfterLoad()` handles backward compatibility and migrations\\n\\n### 5. **Key Files and Locations**\\n\\n**Attach Logic:**\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` â€” main attach implementation\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` â€” comprehensive tests\\n\\n**Session Metadata Validation:**\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/validation/validators.go` â€” ID format validation\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` â€” State structure and normalization\\n\\n**Gemini CLI Agent:**\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/gemini.go` â€” Core agent interface\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/hooks.go` â€” Hook installation (12 hooks)\\n- `/Users/ninawork/